# Local Storage ğŸ’¾

Save data in the browser (persists on refresh).

```javascript
// Save
localStorage.setItem('username', 'Alice');

// Read
const name = localStorage.getItem('username');

// Remove
localStorage.removeItem('username');

// Clear All
localStorage.clear();
```

> âš ï¸ **Note:** Only stores strings! Use `JSON.stringify()` for objects.
